  "text": "Food availability and quality are directly related to suitability of habitat for nonbreeding shorebirds (Escudero et al., 2012; [CITATION_1] , as only abundant and/or high quality food can sustain shorebirds if climatic conditions are unfavourable [CITATION_2] . Sanderlings have been reported to use a wide variety of food sources, including arthropods and polychaetes (Perez-Hurtado, Goss-Custard & Garcia, 1997; Petracci, 2002; Castro et al., 2009 ). Foraging conditions have been shown to shape migratory patterns in shorebirds (Nebel, 2007; Mathot, Smith & Elner, 2007; Catry et al., 2012; Alves et al., 2013b) .",
